According to data published by the PREP, the difference between the first and second positions in the governor's elections is less than 27%. So far, 879 out of 6074 constituencies have not been counted.
This year's elections in Michoacán, where, in line with the data published by the Preliminary Elections Programme (PREP), the difference between the first and second positions in the Governor's election was not yet counted by 879 votes in total of 6074 constituencies.
In this context, the Chairman of the General Council of the electoral Institute in Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that several days ago, on 9 November, the electoral body approved a number of measures that should harmonise local standards with federal electoral reform.
As mentioned above, Michoacán officially did not confirm his political constitution or his State Electoral Code or the electoral Justice Act. For the State Congress approved the reforms shortly before the legal deadline for their entry into force was due to expire, and Governor Leonel Godoy Rangel abandoned their publication within the time limit set in the Act of the Official State Journal, stating that he had any objections to them.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court (SCJN) resolved a constitutional dispute initiated by the local legislative authority and declared the voice of the head of state in the case of constitutional reforms invalid and illegal - because he has no right to approve or veto them -
On the question of the possibility of summarising the vote, María de los Ángeles Llanderal replied that it would be possible, thanks to the approval of the relevant measures by the General Council of the IEM, to carry out a partial and total census by the local electoral authority.
In this way, a partial count of votes, one or more electoral packages, can be carried out under the following conditions: the electoral results do not agree; there is no record of the number of votes and calculation in the relevant box or is not available to the chairman; or if there are errors and obvious violations of the electoral results.
In addition, the total recalculation of votes in all polls will be possible if there is an indication indicating that the difference between the potential winner of the elections and the candidate in second place is smaller or equal to one percentage point; whenever at the beginning of the session the express request of the party representative and/or coalition that proposed the candidate in second place.
The total recalculation of votes will also be possible if, after a proper summation, it is found that the difference between the likely winner and the candidate in the second place is equal or less than one percentage point and also whenever there is an explicit request from a political party whose candidate ended in second place. In such a case, the electoral packages for which a partial census has been made will be eliminated.
It should be noted that in such a situation there is a election in Morelia, where, according to the PREP, the difference between the first and second places is less than 0.16%, even though 129 of the total 923 constituencies have not yet been counted.
